<p>How to install on Linux</p>
<p>Weighbridge requires a running sql server (Mysql or Mariadb )to be
installed properly. 
</p>
<ul>
	<li/>
<p>Unpack the downloaded pack.</p>
	<li/>
<p>Set a link to the executable file.</p>
	<li/>
<p>Run it.</p>
</ul>
<p>The pop up menu you will enter the follwing ifo:</p>
<ol>
	<li/>
<p>Database: enter the database name you created in mysql.
	eg., Weighbridge</p>
	<li/>
<p>Host: server computer name, localhost</p>
	<li/>
<p>Port: 3306 unless you have chaged default ort number for
	mysql 
	</p>
	<li/>
<p>User Name: the name you want to run the weighbridge
	application under in mysql</p>
	<li/>
<p>Password.</p>
</ol>
<p>Note: all the above can be created either directly on mysql or
using an application as phpmyAdmin</p>
